table.description:
Our English cottage home located in the heart of Mont Albert/Box Hill is conveniently located only a few minutes from all that the area has to offer. Enjoy the gastronomy of local cafes and restaurants, or head to Box Hill Central nearby for your shopping and entertainment needs.

[Welcome]
Welcome to our English cottage themed home filled with historical charm. Upon entry, a cosy living room welcomes you. The space has been thoughtfully fitted, including a couch that can covert into a sofabed if required. The adjoining dining area can accommodate 6 and is perfect for your entertaining needs. The recently renovated kitchen is equipped with all the essentials you will require for your convenient and comfort. 
The living room has an airconditioning unit for you to cool down in summer or warm up in winter. As we are environmentally conscious, we would greatly appreciate it if you ensure it is turned off when not in use. We hope you enjoy our home as much as we do! 

[Bedrooms]
Two bedrooms contain queen-sized beds, and the third bedroom has a single-sized bed. Both beds come with clean and freshly pressed linen and all-seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. The living room also has a sofabed which can be converted to accommodate the extra guest or two. 

[Sofabed]
Linen and blanket for the sofabed will only be provided upon request. This request will need to be put in at least 24 hours before check-in. Last-minute requests for sofa bed linen will incur an additional surcharge of $30.

[Bathroom]
There are two bathrooms in total and they are both prepared with complimentary body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for your stay. Toilet paper and bath towels are also included. You are also welcomed to use the iron, washing machine and clothes dryer during your stay. Please note that the quantity of bathroom supplies provided will allow you to comfortably settle in for the initial few days of your stay.

[Carpark]
The private garage can accommodate 2 cars. If you have additional cars with you, you may park along the street outside the property.

Guests will have access to the entire home and parking is available on-site (a charge applies). 


[Check-in]
- CHECK-IN: Standard check-in is between 3-9pm. 

[Check-out]
- CHECK-OUT: Check-out is strictly by 10 am (LATE CHECK-OUTs WILL INCUR A FEE OF $100).

Once your booking has been confirmed, our housing manual will be sent to your email address, containing all information related to your booking. Please refer to that for check-in and check-out instructions.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

Located in the heart Mont Albert, our home is centrally located to offer you all that the area has to offer. Located a mere 5min drive from Box Hill Central, you will find a plethora of dining, shopping and entertainment options a short commute away.

There is a tram stop located outside the home that will take you to Box Hill Central or into the CBD. Mont Albert train station is a short 10min walk away.

[Excess Rubbish]
Please dispose of excess rubbish in the big bins located outside the home.

[Strict House Rules]
- No smoking or drug use allowed (violation will incur a $500 fine).
- No parties allowed.
- No pets allowed.
- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.
- PLEASE USE THE RANGE HOOD WHEN COOKING so as to not set off the smoke alarm. 
- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.

[LOST & FOUND]
-Lost items will be kept in our office for 1 week. $50 will be charged for postage to mail the item back to you upon request.

This is the most affordable, luxurious, and spacious apartment in the Heart of Melbourne without having to sacrifice privacy.

With a Walk Score of 100/100, my home is surrounded by Melbourne's Top Restaurants, Cafes, Bars, Shopping and Entertainment. Whether it be Melbourne's secret hidden laneways, late night hotspots, day-time activities, or education institutions, my place is at the Heart of it all!

Oh, and Melbourne's best Karaoke at K-Box is next door!

The BEDROOMS come with clean luxury linens and all seasons quilts to keep you warm throughout the year. The main bedroom contains a queen sized bed, and the second bedroom a double bed. Both bedrooms come with high quality mattresses and comfortable bedding. There is sufficient storage space for your belongings and hangers for your clothes.

The BATHROOMS are stocked with body wash, hand soap, shampoo and conditioner for you and your group. We also provide toilet paper and bath towels. In the bathroom there is also a washing machine and dryer, detergent, an iron and an ironing board.

The KITCHEN is fully equipped with basic cooking items, such as pots and pans, kettle, microwave, gas stovetop, oven, toaster, cutlery, dining ware and some basic condiments for you to use.

Free WIFI throughout your stay, available in all rooms. The WIFI details are in the manual provided.

Ongoing communication is best via the platform or through the phone number provided. Please provide us with your name and reservation address if you do call us, and we'll be at your assistance.

The location is ideal for all travellers with Russell Street downstairs, 2-min walk to Melbourne Central Station (hotspot) and Chinatown (hotspot), a 5-min walk to Queen Victoria Market, access to Elizabeth Street's Asian eateries, Melbourne's GPO and Hardware Lane are down the road, Emporium and Flinders Street are a free tram-ride away.

We highly recommend walking next-door to K-Box for an affordable Karaoke session with some drinks any night of the week!

I would definitely walk everywhere! How else would you get to see all of Melbourne's laneways, alleys, side streets and hidden spots? But if you want, there is free tram access in all directions on La Trobe Street and down on Swanston Street, as well as Melbourne Central's Train Station just a 5-7 minute walk away!

- The correct number of guests staying must be reflected in the booking. Linen and towels will only be provided for the number of guests included in the booking. 
- Please leave the property in a similar condition as it was during check-in. 
- Breakages, damages, theft and loss will be the guest's liability and responsibility.
- Violation of any of the rules will result in a loss of your security deposit and/or additional charges.
- As part of our verification procedure, a photo of a government-issued ID and a selfie may be requested.
- Noise levels are to be kept at an appropriate level at all times.
- Please dispose of excess rubbish according to the rubbish disposal instructions located in the Housing Manual.

- We provide a set of toiletries to ensure you are settled in well for the initial period of your stay. Regrettably, we are unable to provide re-stocks or refills of these toiletries if you have a longer stay. You may, however, request for housekeeping during your stay at additional cost.
